com.esri.mo2.map.img
Interface ImageServer

All Superinterfaces:
Dataset, GeoDataset, ImageClass, MapDataset, Searchable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseImageServer
public interface ImageServer
extends ImageClass

Provides support for an ImageServerLayer by managing retrieval of map images from ArcIMS ImageServer. Images are normally retrieved from the ImageServer by sending a request via HTTP using a URL having a format that is appropriate for the particular server. Optionally, Images may be cached to provide immediate feedback when the Map is panned or zoomed, while image retrieval is occuring.

See Also:
Image

retrieve

public void retrieve(Tile tile)
The associated Cache will call this method in a separate Thread when it wants to obtain more data. This method should do all the retrieval work that would normally be performed within a MapDataset's search method.

Parameters:
tile - the cache tile that should be given the retrieved data
